{{italic title}}
'''''Paint This with Jerry Yarnell''''' is an educational television show produced by Jerry Yarnell, owner of the Yarnell School of Fine Art. It is broadcast primarily on [[Public broadcasting#television|public television]] channels. The show focuses mostly on [[Landscape painting|landscape]], [[wildlife]], and Western American themes, in the [[Impressionism|impressionist]] style. The [[List of art mediums|media]] used are: [[Acrylic paint|acrylics]], [[Water miscible oil paint|water miscible oils]] and [[Watercolor painting|watercolors]].

==Format==
Most of the episodes are in groups which cover instructions and demonstrations for a single example painting. All episodes are 30 minutes in length.
